snippet.textDisplay: Does anyone else agree with me that there are basically only three names for short female hairstyles - pixie, bowl cut and mullet? Brad please make a video either like “pixie or not a pixie” where we review some short female hairstyles, or a video with just coming up with new names for short hairstyles. snippet.textDisplay:
speaking of bond builders... what's a good quality one you could purchase without a license? preferably the ones you use during processing, not the hair mask types (although if there's some miracle mask out there I'm all ears)
as much as I love dropping $400+ at the salon... I've been getting my hair dyed for so long while also experimenting a lot at home, that now I don't have to go out for every single touch up, but I miss the bond builders they use, even if they only marginally help.


ps- nothing has dramatically changed my hair (for the better) as much as not washing it frequently. BUT now that my hair only touches water every new decade I'm not getting in many hair masks/deep conditioning treatments. I'm considering just wetting the shaft->ends to apply the masks more often. suggestions anyone? <3
